2021 in March: 20 packages for every household - and a jump in weight
46.6 million parcels arrived in Israel during 2021 - similar to 2020
The average weight per package stands at 435 grams - a jump of 36% compared to 2020
The busiest month: December, when the average package weighed 524 grams.
In 2021, 46.6 million postal packages arrived in Israel, almost 20 packages on average per household - according to Israel Post data obtained by Israel Today.
The number of packages that arrived in 2021 is similar to 2020, when 46.5 million packages arrived in Israel, and lower than 2019 - when 61.6 million packages arrived.
However, this year there was a jump of more than 36 percent year over year in the weight of packages from abroad.
In 2021, 20,253 tons of products arrived in Israel from abroad, a jump of 36% compared to 14,860 tons in 2020, and 16,743 tons in 2019.
Changes in consumption habits
The average weight of a package has jumped 60 percent in two years - from 272 grams in 2019 to 435 grams in 2021.
The increase in package weight is mainly influenced by two main trends, both from the seller and the buyer side: the large overseas shopping sites are uniting items for one delivery and no longer send each product from the shopping cart in a separate package.
On the Israeli consumer side, the fast delivery of the shipments, within a few days of ordering, supports the purchase of more everyday products such as clothing and gifts, which the buyers want to receive near the purchase.
In 2021, as in 2020 and 2019, the month with the highest number of packages from abroad is December, with 4.2 million packages weighing a total of 2,200 tons.
In December the average weight of a package was 1,800 pounds [524 g], 20 percent higher than the annual average.
Black Friday effect
More packages arrived in December than any other month, likely in the wake of November's shopping holidays, such as Chinese Singles' Day, Black Friday and Cyber Monday.
The big orders start arriving in Israel a week or two after the purchase.
